        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1523570685" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17632801766301261523">Anyone that is able to get through this without showing the slightest bit of emotion is not a human being. A remarkable story of a remarkable man, so full of life one minute and reduced to movement in one eye the next, a haunting, harrowing look inside the mind of a person with locked-in syndrome you would think this would end up as a rant of anger and &quot;why did this happen to me&quot;, but his dignified manner and spirit was truly inspirational and caught me out at just how uplifting it would turn ou</span>
  <span id="freeText17632801766301261523" style="display:none">Anyone that is able to get through this without showing the slightest bit of emotion is not a human being. A remarkable story of a remarkable man, so full of life one minute and reduced to movement in one eye the next, a haunting, harrowing look inside the mind of a person with locked-in syndrome you would think this would end up as a rant of anger and "why did this happen to me", but his dignified manner and spirit was truly inspirational and caught me out at just how uplifting it would turn out to be, although of course it still remained very moving. Two days after the book was published, Bauby was to died of pneumonia, but this is a lasting tribute that is definitely worth reading. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17632801766301261523" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

