<span id="freeTextContainer3868374139324225626">E S A R I N T U L O M D P C F B V H G J Q Z Y X K W<br/><br/><i>More than an alphabet, it is a hit parade in which each letter is placed according to the frequency of its use in the French language.</i> <br/><br/>Imagine being incapable of movement or speech and finding the only way to communicate is by blinking your left eye. Jean-Dominique Bauby wrote <i>The Diving Bell and The Butterfly</i>, via a transcriber after suffering a major stroke, one blink at a time. <br/><br/>The only thing Bauby has left is his mind, so he uses it. <br/><br/>3.5</span>

