        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer920267370" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4252050449333182816"><a href='http://kiribear.blogspot.com' rel='nofollow noopener'>Check out my blog to see Reviews of Book and Movies, and check out some Recipes!</a><br/><br/>This was definitely a quick and interesting read. I have actually never seen the movie, and this was my first time getting around to reading the book. The write Jean-Dominique Bauby wrote with the aid of a &quot;translator&quot; that had to have taken an extensive amount of time. Jean-Dominique, former editor in chief of Elle magazine, becomes a quadriplegic after a stroke affects his brain stem. He can only communicate in a t</span>
  <span id="freeText4252050449333182816" style="display:none"><a href="http://kiribear.blogspot.com" rel="nofollow noopener">Check out my blog to see Reviews of Book and Movies, and check out some Recipes!</a><br /><br />This was definitely a quick and interesting read. I have actually never seen the movie, and this was my first time getting around to reading the book. The write Jean-Dominique Bauby wrote with the aid of a "translator" that had to have taken an extensive amount of time. Jean-Dominique, former editor in chief of Elle magazine, becomes a quadriplegic after a stroke affects his brain stem. He can only communicate in a type of one eye blinking to make it through an altered alphabet. He suffers from what is known as "locked-in" syndrome in which the brain is still functioning at normal, but the body is not responding as it should. <br /><br />The fact that this book even exists at all given his condition is quite fascinating. Just the implications of what it took to write the book are insane. It was snippets of his current and past life woven together in what seems like a short novel to us, but undoubtedly was an immense amount of time and effort upon him and his "translator". <br /><br />A solid 4 stars, and worth reading, just for his effort of writing it.</span>
